  <!-- SECTION 1: WHAT IS -->
  <div class="sec-mark" id="what-is">DEFINITION</div>
  <div class="prose">
    <h2>What is Shopify Server-Side Tracking?</h2>
    <p>Server-side tracking (also called Conversions API, server-to-server tracking, or S2S tracking) sends conversion events directly from your web server to advertising platforms &mdash; completely bypassing the customer&rsquo;s browser. Instead of relying on a JavaScript pixel in the browser to fire when a purchase completes, a webhook fires from Shopify&rsquo;s backend the moment payment is confirmed, routing event data directly to Meta&rsquo;s Conversions API, Google&rsquo;s Enhanced Conversions endpoint, and TikTok&rsquo;s Events API.</p>
    <p>The key distinction is where the event originates. A browser pixel depends on the customer&rsquo;s device: their browser settings, installed extensions, network conditions, and whether they accepted your cookie banner. A server event originates from Shopify&rsquo;s infrastructure &mdash; it fires regardless of what the customer&rsquo;s browser does, making it immune to ad blockers, iOS privacy restrictions, and Safari&rsquo;s Intelligent Tracking Prevention.</p>
    <h3>Server-side vs browser pixel: the architecture</h3>
  </div>
